===message:You have some excellent points in your statement, but I don't feel that you addressed the major issue which was slavery.  The confederate states were not so worried about a national banking system and gold to seperate from the union.  They were more concerned about the national government moving toward abolishing slavery in the states.  The issue was the rights and powers of the states to have slaves, not so much as the banking system which you elaborated on.  The civil war was basically fought over the institution of slavery.
=========yorg=========
